# `Dregg2.Crypto.MlDsaSignReal` — the REAL full-byte ML-DSA-65 SIGN core (FIPS 204 Algorithm 7
`ML-DSA.Sign_internal`, deterministic variant `rnd = 0`), as EXECUTABLE `def`s.

This is the honest close for SIGN: the counterpart to `MlDsaVerifyReal.verifyCore`. Where the verifier
recomputes the challenge and checks it, `signCore` runs the FULL Fiat–Shamir-with-aborts rejection loop and
emits a real 3309-byte ML-DSA-65 signature. It is Lean-only — nothing in `dregg-pq`/`node` is touched. A
follow-up wires its FFI and routes `MlDsaKey::sign` through it (the brick-8 analog).

It REUSES — reimplements nothing that exists — the landed, gate-verified bricks:

* BRICK 1 `Dregg2.Crypto.Keccak` — real SHAKE-256 (`shake256`), byte-exact vs FIPS 202 KATs.
* BRICK 2 `Dregg2.Crypto.MlDsaRing` — the ring `R_q = ℤ_q[X]/(X²⁵⁶+1)` with the gate-verified NTT
  (`ntt`/`intt`/`pointwiseMul` proven equal to the schoolbook negacyclic product).
* BRICK 3 `Dregg2.Crypto.MlDsaSampleInBall` — `SampleInBall` (τ = 49), cross-impl KAT-pinned.
* BRICK 4 `Dregg2.Crypto.MlDsaExpandA` — `ExpandA` (Â ∈ R_q^{6×5}, NTT domain), corner-KAT-pinned.
* BRICK 5 `Dregg2.Crypto.MlDsaCodec` — `unpackBits`/`packBits`, the `z` sign map `zCoeffFromField`,
  `sigEncode`, `hintEncode` — all round-trip-pinned on REAL crate bytes.
* BRICK 6 `Dregg2.Crypto.MlDsaVerifyReal` — `decompose`/`highBits` (the centered `mod± α` rounding),
  `w1Encode`, `infNormZ` (the verifier's gate uses exactly these; sign shares them).

## THE ALGORITHM (FIPS 204 Algorithm 7, deterministic `rnd = 0`, ML-DSA-65)

`skDecode(sk)` (Alg 24): `ρ(32) ‖ K(32) ‖ tr(64) ‖ s1(ℓ·BitPack η) ‖ s2(k·BitPack η) ‖ t0(k·BitPack d)`.
Each `s1`/`s2` poly is 128 bytes (η = 4, 4 bits/coeff, `BitUnpack(·, η, η)` ⇒ coeff `= η − field`); each
`t0` poly is 416 bytes (13 bits/coeff, `BitUnpack(·, 2^{d−1}−1, 2^{d−1})` ⇒ coeff `= 2^{d−1} − field`).

`expandMask(ρ', κ)` (Alg 34): for `r = 0..ℓ−1`, `y[r] = BitUnpack(SHAKE256(ρ' ‖ (κ+r) as 2 LE bytes), γ₁)`
at `c = 1 + bitlen(γ₁−1) = 20` bits/coeff — the SAME 20-bit sign map as the `z` codec (`zCoeffFromField`).

`signCore(sk, msg, ctx)`:
* `μ = H(tr ‖ 0x00 ‖ |ctx| ‖ ctx ‖ msg, 64)`;  `ρ' = H(K ‖ rnd ‖ μ, 64)` with `rnd = {0}³²` (deterministic).
* Loop `κ = 0, ℓ, 2ℓ, …`:  `y = expandMask ρ' κ`;  `w = NTT⁻¹(Â ∘ NTT(y))`;  `w1 = HighBits(w)`;
  `c̃ = H(μ ‖ w1Encode(w1), 48)`;  `c = SampleInBall(c̃)`;  `z = y + c·s1`;  `(r1, r0) = Decompose(w − c·s2)`.
* Reject (retry `κ += ℓ`) if `‖z‖∞ ≥ γ₁ − β` or `‖r0‖∞ ≥ γ₂ − β`.
* `h = MakeHint(−c·t0, w − c·s2 + c·t0)`;  reject if `‖c·t0‖∞ ≥ γ₂` or `#(h = 1) > ω`.
* else return `sigEncode(c̃, z, h)`.

ML-DSA-65: `k = 6, ℓ = 5, γ₁ = 2¹⁹, γ₂ = (q−1)/32, β = 196, ω = 55, τ = 49, η = 4, d = 13, q = 8380417`.

## THE ANTI-FAKE GATE (`native_decide` over NIST-PUBLISHED ACVP FIPS 204 vectors)

`acvpSk`/`acvpPk`/`acvpMsg`/`acvpCtx`/`acvpSig` are transcribed VERBATIM from NIST ACVP-Server (https://github.com/usnistgov/ACVP-Server), file
`gen-val/json-files/ML-DSA-sigGen-FIPS204/internalProjection.json`, `testGroups` entry `tgId = 3`
(`testType = "AFT"`, `parameterSet = "ML-DSA-65"`, `deterministic = true`,
`signatureInterface = "external"`, `preHash = "pure"`), test case `tcId = 36`.
That group is the DETERMINISTIC (`rnd = 0`) EXTERNAL-interface pure variant -- exactly the semantics
`signCore` implements (`M' = 0x00 ‖ |ctx| ‖ ctx ‖ msg`, `rnd = 0`). The bytes are NOT crate output and NOT
hand-written; the KAT ANCHOR is NIST.

* `sign_matches_acvp_deterministic` — `signCore acvpSk acvpMsg acvpCtx = acvpSig` (BYTE-EXACT vs NIST's
  expected signature). If ExpandMask, the rejection loop, MakeHint, skDecode, or the `M'` framing were
  wrong this reds.
* `sign_produces_valid_sig` — `MlDsaVerifyReal.verifyCore acvpPk acvpMsg acvpCtx (signCore …) = true`
  — our own verified verifier ACCEPTS the Lean-produced signature (cross-brick soundness).

READ THE STATEMENTS, NOT THIS PROSE. Both gates are SINGLE-VECTOR KATs closed by `native_decide`; neither
contains a `forall`. They show agreement with the NIST reference on ONE input -- evidence, not a
correctness proof. The for-all-inputs obligation is `SignCoreSpec`.

`native_decide` runs the COMPILED `def`s (the rejection loop runs compiled — expected). Trusted base is
`Lean.ofReduceBool` + `Lean.trustCompiler`, the same residual every other brick names. No `sorry`, no user
`axiom`, no toy substitute.
-/

